sentence: Among the underlying components of the S&P 500 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD), where a total of 26,072 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 2.6 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 58.7% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month of 4.4 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $110 strike put option expiring August 21, 2015 , with 2,099 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 209,900 underlying shares of HD.

Monster Beverage Corp (Symbol: MNST) options are showing a volume of 6,954 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 695,400 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 55.3% of MNST's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 1.3 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $150 strike call option expiring August 14, 2015 , with 928 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 92,800 underlying shares of MNST.

That number of contracts represents approximately 1.4 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 47.9% of UA's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.0 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $90 strike put option expiring September 04, 2015 , with 1,969 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 196,900 underlying shares of UA.
